				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You don't have to write various reset stubs with repeated code. That's redundant and prone to errors. You can make an include file with the stub, and call the label <strong>-reset_stub</strong>, so that the assembler doesn't complain about repeated labels, and then for the vectors you can just use <strong>.word vblank, -reset_stub, irq</strong>, still inside the include file, to completely get rid of redundancy. Just include that file at the end of every bank.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
							<td class="gensmall" align="right">
							
